SUMMARY:Tri Kappa Exhibition – Celebrating 125 Years
DESCRIPTION:Tri Kappa 125th Anniversary \nOpening Exhibition Reception \nBrown County Art Guild   \nFebruary 22, 2026  \n2-4pm / Remarks at 3pm  \nCelebrate 125 years of Tri Kappa at the opening reception of a special exhibition drawn from the Tri Kappa Art Collection. Featuring works by Indiana artists, this exhibition honors Tri-Kappa’s long-standing commitment to the arts. Join us in celebrating the exhibition and Tri Kappa’s historic anniversary.  Light refreshments will be served. \nFree & open to the public.   \n Tri Kappa 125th Anniversary Exhibition  \nFebruary 22 – June 26, 2026    \nBrown County Art Guild                           \n \nJoin us in celebrating 125 years of Tri Kappa and its rich art collection.\nSince its inception in 1901, Tri Kappa has served as a cornerstone of Indiana’s cultural landscape, fostering a legacy of charity, culture, and education that spans generations. The Guild will showcase a curated selection of paintings from the Tri-Kappa collection, highlighting the talents of Indiana artists, past and present. Discover works that reflect the beauty, creativity, and enduring spirit of our state’s artistic heritage. \n\nBrown County Art Guild – A not for profit organization located in the heart of downtown Nashville, Indiana.  On display throughout its galleries is a prized collection of historic paintings as well as current works for sale from regional award-winning member artists.  The Guild also offers artist demonstrations, workshops, and a variety of events or programs throughout the year.   \nWinter Hours – January & February 2026, Monday-Wednesday closed or by appt.~ Thursday-Saturday, 11am-5pm ~ Sunday, 12-4pm  \nMarch – December 2026, Monday – Saturday 11am-5pm & Sundays 12-4pm \n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/tri-kappa-exhibition-celebrating-125-years/
ORGANIZER;CN=Brown County Art Guild:MAILTO:admin@bcartguild.org
CATEGORIES:Art Events &amp; Exhibits,Family Friendly,Free,Happening
LOCATION:Brown County Art Guild, South Van Buren Street, Nashville, IN
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://browncounty.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/J5UkpobD.jpg
END:VEVENT
