SUMMARY:Centennial Victorian Tea
DESCRIPTION:After 25 continuous years of hosting our beloved annual Victorian Tea, paused during the pandemic, the Brown County Art Gallery is proud to bring this tradition back one last time with a very special Centennial Tea, celebrating 100 years of the Gallery (founded in 1926).\nGuests will enjoy an elegant tea service featuring an assortment of delicious tea fare, a special favor, door prizes, and a raffle, including a beautiful painting by Gallery artist Jodie Friend.\nThe afternoon will also include a one-act play, “Selma and the Painter,” performed by Broadway actress Jill Tasker, telling the beautiful love story of renowned artist T.C. Steele and the woman behind his legendary career.\n This promises to be a memorable and meaningful celebration of art, history, and tradition.\nReservations are required.\n $50 per person\nFor more information or to reserve your spot, visit\n https://browncountyartgallery.org/ ( https://browncountyartgallery.org/ ) or call (812) 988-4609 ( tel:8129884609 ).\n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/centennial-victorian-tea/
ORGANIZER;CN=Historic Brown County Art Gallery:MAILTO:
