SUMMARY:Teutonic: The Brahms Piano Trios
DESCRIPTION:\nChamberFest Brown County presents Teutonic: The Brahms Piano Trios.\nA rare opportunity to hear Brahms’ three magnificent piano trios in one concert: music of unmatched emotional range and complexity. Not for the faint-hearted!\nBrahms: Piano Trio no. 1, op. 8Brahms: Piano Trio no. 2, op. 87Brahms: Piano Trio no. 3, op. 101\nArtists\n\n​Andreas Ioannides, piano\nMadalyn Parnas Möller, violin\nMaurice Neuman, cello\n\n\n\nThis concert is sponsored by the Eads family in memory of Ralph S. (Tony) Eads.\n\n
