SUMMARY:Pastorale: Strings and Winds
DESCRIPTION:ChamberFest Brown County presents a star-studded lineup featuring Chicago Symphony Orchestra musicians present an uplifting program of music for the outdoors: radiant, folksy, uplifting.\n​​​​​Beethoven: Sextet for 2 horns and string quartet, op. 81bSpohr: Octet, op. 32Dvorak: String Quintet, op. 97\n​Artists\n\n​Qing Hou, violin\nLei Hou, violin\nLarry Neuman, viola\nAurlien Pederzoli, viola\nBrandon Vamos, cello\nJim Campbell, clarinet\nJim Smelser, horn\nOto Carrilla, horn\nAlex Horton, bass\n\n
